     =========================================================
     Geant4 - an Object-Oriented Toolkit for Simulation in HEP
     =========================================================

                            gammaray_telescope
                            ------------------
                     F.Longo, R.Giannitrapani & G.Santin

gammaray_telescope is an example of application of Geant4 in a space envinronment.


  
0. Setting up the environment variables

setenv G4SYSTEM Linux-g++      # works correctly only on Linux 
setenv G4INSTALL $G4HOME/geant4
setenv OGLHOME "/usr/local" 
setenv OGLLIBS "-L$OGLHOME/lib -lMesaGLU -lMesaGL" # OPENGL visualization


setenv LHCXXTOP /afs/cern.ch/sw/lhcxx # to use AIDA interface (at CERN only!)
setenv PLATF redhat61
source $LHCXXTOP/share/LHCXX/3.0.0/install/sharedstart.csh 

set path = ( $G4INSTALL/bin/$G4SYSTEM $G4WORKDIR/bin/$G4SYSTEM $path )

setenv G4VIS_BUILD_OPENGLX_DRIVER 1
setenv G4VIS_BUILD_DAWN_DRIVER         1  # DAWN is the Fukui Renderer
setenv G4VIS_BUILD_DAWNFILE_DRIVER     1  
setenv G4VIS_BUILD_RAYX_DRIVER         1  # GEANT4 Ray Tracing
setenv G4VIS_BUILD_VRML_DRIVER         1  # Spawns VRML viewer
setenv G4VIS_BUILD_VRMLFILE_DRIVER     1  # Writes VRML ascii file

setenv G4UI_BUILD_GAG_SESSION 1

setenv G4UI_USE_GAG           1
setenv G4VIS_USE_OPENGLX      1
setenv G4VIS_USE_DAWN         1
setenv G4VIS_USE_DAWNFILE     1
setenv G4VIS_USE_RAYX         1
setenv G4VIS_USE_VRML         1
setenv G4VIS_USE_VRMLFILE     1

0.5 Sample run

 To execute a sample simulation with visualisation of gamma tracks
 interacting with the detector in its standard configuration run:

 GammaRayTel 

 It is possible also to run two different configuration defined in macro1.mac 
 and macro2.mac.

1. Detector description

 The detector is defined in GammaRayTelDetectorConstruction.cc
 It is composed of a Payload with three main detectors, a Tracker (TKR), a
 Calorimeter (CAL) and an Anticoincidence system (ACD). 

 The standard configuration is made of a TKR of 15 Layers of Si detectors, 
 with Lead Converter; a CAL of 8 layers of CsI. 4 lateral panels and a top 
 layer of plastic scintillator (ACT and ACL) complete the configuration.

 It is possible to vary this configuration using the commands defined in 
 GammaRayTelDetectorMessenger.cc

2. Physics processes

 This example uses the standard Electromagnetic processes.

3. Particle Generator Action

 The GammaRayTelParticleGenerationAction and its Messenger let the user define
 the incident flux of particles, from a specific direction or from an 
 isotropic background. The user can define also between two spectral options:
 monochromatic or with a power-law dependence.

4. ReadOutGeometry

 The tracker is made of Silicon Microstrips detectors. The ReadOut geometry
 provides the description of the strips.

5. Hit 

 In this version only the hits from the TKR are recorded.

6. Histogramming

 The track is visualized using AIDA interfaces.

  






